{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/33/comments/40176977.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/33#comment-40176977"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse/issues/33.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 33, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/lyse.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/lyse"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}ts=249921"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "lyse", "full_name": "labscript_suite/lyse", "uuid": "{55eebdfe-43d1-4ae8-9049-50c55b295397}"}, "title": "Lyse freezes on selection"}, "content": {"raw": "Found a solution:\nIf we block all signals during ```update_row``` things run smoothly.\n\nSo I added  this to the top of ```update_row```:\n```\n#!python\nself._model.blockSignals(True)\n```\n\nAnd this to the bottom of ```update_row```:\n```\n#!python\n        self._model.blockSignals(False)\n        self._model.layoutChanged.emit()\n```\nI'm not sure if there are any downsides to this so I'll test a bit before creating a pull request.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Found a solution:\nIf we block all signals during <code>update_row</code> things run smoothly.</p>\n<p>So I added  this to the top of <code>update_row</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-python\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">_model</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">blockSignals</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">True</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>And this to the bottom of <code>update_row</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-python\"><pre><span></span>        <span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">_model</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">blockSignals</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">False</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">_model</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">layoutChanged</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">emit</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>I'm not sure if there are any downsides to this so I'll test a bit before creating a pull request.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-09-28T16:08:59.897510+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jan Werkmann", "uuid": "{44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:a70cc9cf-684e-4849-a61a-9ade4d7218b5/07e5095a-4741-4dc0-a462-9c7d455f961d/128"}}, "nickname": "PhyNerd", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:a70cc9cf-684e-4849-a61a-9ade4d7218b5"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 40176977}